	<span class="anthracite size13" contentbodystyle="Anthracite">Something I'm surprised about - a company doesn't run that kind of computer power just to provide a game universe for free. So why hasn't any effort been made to translate the Trotsky's userid into a real-life name and credit card?

If Trotsky doesn't map to a paying user, then you've narrowed your suspect list to those who currently logged in to the system through company userids ... and mightn't there be some way to track their processes and/or debug userids? 

I'm catching up to this story, haven't gotten to the latest entry yet, but had to post this anyhow. Seems a very obvious avenue of investigation has been totally overlooked.

